  <constraints>
    <constraint source="ADR-001">.NET 8 Minimal API patterns. No Azure Functions. Endpoints registered via Minimal API `Map*` calls.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-008">Endpoint-filter authorization (`.AddEndpointFilter&lt;...&gt;()`) MUST apply on every Action endpoint. NO global middleware for resource checks. G11 verified by grep audit.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-010">Endpoint registration goes through `MapActionEndpoints()` extension method registered in `EndpointMappingExtensions.cs` â€” NOT inline in Program.cs.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-013">Endpoints depend on `IActionEngineFacade` (PublicContracts) where possible; internal types (`IActionOrchestrationService` from task 041) are accessed via the facade boundary, not direct injection from any CRUD-side caller.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-016">Endpoints carry `EnableRateLimiting("ai-action-invocation")` attribute slot for task 044 to wire concrete policy. Soft enforcement MVP.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-019">Every error path returns `Results.Problem(...)` (ProblemDetails RFC 7807) with `statusCode`, `title`, `detail`. NO raw exception messages.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-029">No new NuGet packages unless absolutely required. If added: verify â‰¤5MB compressed publish-size delta + no new HIGH-severity CVE.</constraint>
    <constraint source="bff-extensions.md">Pre-merge checklist binding: placement decision = BFF (cited from spec.md Â§6), publish-size delta verified, no new CRUDâ†’AI direct dependencies (facade used).</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">G11 acceptance gate established here. Every endpoint in ActionEndpoints.cs MUST have an endpoint filter. Verified by grep + adr-check.</constraint>
  </constraints>

