  <steps>
    <step order="0">Context check: confirm working tree clean, branch is `work/ai-spaarke-action-engine-r1`, baseline build passes. Confirm tasks 010 (entities), 014 (BFF module), 015 (PublicContracts facade), 030 (IGateResolver interface) all show âś… in TASK-INDEX.md. (task-execute Step 0)</step>
    <step order="1">Load `.claude/constraints/bff-extensions.md` and answer every pre-merge checklist item in `notes/decisions/task-040-bff-extensions-checklist.md`. Cite placement decision (= BFF per spec.md Â§6).</step>
    <step order="2">Read existing `PlaybookEndpoints.cs` + `AnalysisEndpoints.cs` to capture the canonical endpoint group shape. Read `Filters/DocumentAuthorizationFilter.cs` as the model for the new `ActionResourceAuthorizationFilter.cs`.</step>
    <step order="3">Create `Filters/ActionResourceAuthorizationFilter.cs`: implements `IEndpointFilter`, resolves Action by id from Dataverse (via the `IActionEngineFacade` from task 015), validates tenant scope, checks the caller's right per operation kind (read / write / execute), short-circuits with `Results.Problem(statusCode: 403, title: "Forbidden", detail: ...)` on denial. Inject scoped services per ADR-010 conventions.</step>
    <step order="4">Create `src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Api/Ai/ActionEndpoints.cs` as a static class with `MapActionEndpoints(this IEndpointRouteBuilder app)`. Register the 5 routes (GET/POST/PUT/DELETE/POST-run). Each route: `.AddEndpointFilter&lt;ActionResourceAuthorizationFilter&gt;()` + `.RequireAuthorization()` + `.WithName(...)` + `.WithTags("ActionEngine")` + `.RequireRateLimiting("ai-action-invocation")` (named policy slot for task 044).</step>
    <step order="5">Wire each handler: thin delegation to `IActionEngineFacade` (which task 015 provides). DO NOT inject `IActionOrchestrationService` (internal type from task 041) directly â€” go through the facade so G12 (facade integrity) is preserved. For `/run`, the facade method is `ExecuteActionAsync(actionId, parameters, cancellationToken)` returning a Run id + status; the handler returns 202 Accepted on async paths and 200 OK on synchronous Tool returns.</step>
    <step order="6">Every error path returns `Results.Problem(...)` per ADR-019. Status mapping: not-found â†’ 404; tenant mismatch â†’ 404 (do NOT leak existence across tenants); validation error â†’ 400; auth denial â†’ 403; rate-limit â†’ 429; feature-disabled â†’ 503 (slot for task 045). Title field always set; detail field set; `type` field URI per ADR-019 if available.</step>
    <step order="7">Register `MapActionEndpoints()` in `Infrastructure/DI/EndpointMappingExtensions.cs` in the AI endpoint group section (find the `// AI endpoints` comment around line 157 per plan.md Â§2 Resources).</step>
    <step order="8">Run the grep audit: `grep -nE "Map(Get|Post|Put|Delete)" src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Api/Ai/ActionEndpoints.cs` AND `grep -nE "AddEndpointFilter" src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Api/Ai/ActionEndpoints.cs` â€” confirm every `Map*` call has a matching `AddEndpointFilter` line. Record the audit output verbatim in `notes/spikes/g11-endpoint-filter-grep.md`.</step>
    <step order="9">Build + run focused unit tests: a smoke test that the endpoint group registers (`MapActionEndpoints` extension method exists, route table contains the 5 routes). Integration test: 401 without auth on `/run`; 403 for user lacking `actionExecute`; 200 + Run id for authorized caller (use the `IActionEngineFacade` stub if task 041 isn't merged yet â€” task 041 swaps in the real implementation).</step>
    <step order="9.5">Run quality gates per task-execute Step 9.5: `code-review` on `ActionEndpoints.cs` + `ActionResourceAuthorizationFilter.cs` + the `EndpointMappingExtensions.cs` edit; `adr-check` verifies ADR-008 (endpoint filters on every route), ADR-010 (registration via extension method), ADR-019 (every error path uses `Results.Problem`), ADR-029 (no new NuGet packages without budget check). Re-run `dotnet build src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/` and `dotnet list package --vulnerable --include-transitive | grep -i HIGH` (expect no NEW HIGH; pre-existing Kiota CVE is documented project-level).</step>
    <step order="10">Update `tasks/TASK-INDEX.md`: mark task 040 âś…. Verify it unblocks tasks 041, 042, 043, 044, 045, 052, 053, 054, 055, 060. Reset `current-task.md` for the next active task.</step>
    <step order="11">Document any deviations from this plan in `projects/ai-spaarke-action-engine-r1/notes/handoffs/task-040-handoff.md` and add a brief commit message recap.</step>
  </steps>

